Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of nine (9) years.  That is four (4) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentenced is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Earned Release Program.
Conditions of probation:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) maintain fulltime employment or work search as directed;
3) pay $145.00 restitution to Destinee Pritzl at 2311 Monroe Street, Two Rivers, WI;  within the first 12 months of probation;
4) no contact with Destinee Pritzl, Tanner Cook or Frank Meyer (AKA JR Burt);
5) spend eight (8) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately.  Court will allow NA meetings in the jail;
6) spend an additional two (2) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the court;
7) provide a DNA sample;
8) maintain absolute sobriety;
9) AODA assessment and follow through;
10) defendant is to use one doctor to prescribe medication and use only one pharmacy unless more are approved by the agent;
11) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
12) defendant is to write a letter of apology to the victim.  That letter is to be approved by the agent and the agent will foward the letter to the victim;
13) pay court costs;
14) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Court finds 130 days credit if revoked.
Minutes.
